```julia
function clean_column(col)
    return replace(strip(lowercase(col)), '-' => '_')
end
```

This function first strips any leading or trailing whitespaces using `strip`, then lowercases the string with `lowercase`, and finally replaces any hyphens (`-`) with underscores (`_`) using `replace`. The result is a clean column name in the format you specified, such as "my_column" from the example.
